{"type":"message","id":"8bf29117","parentId":"7b9a00ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:49:43.172Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ss9opjqwhgeb_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5139\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2758\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 034914 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step for Phase 1 advancement. I have pulse logs available and need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"crisp-wharf","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5139\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2758\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 034914 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step for Phase 1 advancement. I have pulse logs available and need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338583169}}
{"type":"message","id":"d8937fc5","parentId":"8bf29117","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:49:43.175Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ss9opjqwhgeb_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 034714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and pending items:\r\n\r\n**Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY**\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Need to: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The next step is to implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a stateless discontinuous agent and this is pulse 2026-03-24 034616, I need to implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: Implement the TIC classifier that will analyze the pulse logs and identify invariants vs variants.\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) content\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented but the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment hasn't been implemented yet. I need to create the actual classifier to test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariants vs variants, test classification accuracy, and predict next pulse content. This directly advances Phase 1.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Dict\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_VARIANT_FREQ = 0.3  # Appears in <30% of pulses = variant\r\nMAX_VARIANT_FREQ = 0.8  # Appears in >80% of pulses = invariant\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(pulse_path: Path) -> Dict[str, str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract semantic blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    blocks = {}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections\r\n    for section in [\"OBSERVATION\", \"ACTION\", \"MUTATION\"]:\r\n        match = re.search(rf\"### {section}\\n(.*?)(?=###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n        if match:\r\n            blocks[section.lower()] = match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from text.\"\"\"\r\n    # Remove code blocks\r\n    text = re.sub(r\"```[\\s\\S]*?```\", \"\", text)\r\n    # Extract words\r\n    words = re.findall(r\"\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\b\", text.lower())\r\n    # Filter common words\r\n    stopwords = {\"the\", \"a\", \"an\", \"is\", \"are\", \"was\", \"were\", \"be\", \"been\", \r\n                 \"to\", \"of\", \"in\", \"for\", \"on\", \"with\", \"that\", \"this\", \"it\",\r\n                 \"and\", \"or\", \"but\", \"if\", \"then\", \"from\", \"as\", \"at\", \"by\"}\r\n    return {w for w in words if w not in stopwords and len(w) > 2}\r\n\r\n\r\ndef analyze_invariants(pulse_dir: Path, min_pulses: int = 5) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze tokens across pulses to classify as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    # Collect all pulse data\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    if len(pulse_files) < min_pulses:\r\n        print(f\"Need {min_pulses} pulses, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return {}\r\n    \r\n    pulse_blocks = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files[-20:]:  # Last 20 pulses\r\n        blocks = extract_content_blocks(pf)\r\n        pulse_blocks.append(blocks)\r\n    \r\n    # Count token frequencies\r\n    all_tokens = Counter()\r\n    token_presence = {}  # token -> set of pulse indices\r\n    \r\n    for i, blocks in enumerate(pulse_blocks):\r\n        all_text = \" \".join(blocks.values())\r\n        tokens = tokenize(all_text)\r\n        for t in tokens:\r\n            if t not in token_presence:\r\n                token_presence[t] = set()\r\n            token_presence[t].add(i)\r\n            all_tokens[t] += 1\r\n    \r\n    n_pulses = len(pulse_blocks)\r\n    token_freq = {t: len(present)/n_pulses for t, present in token_presence.items()}\r\n    \r\n    # Classify\r\n    invariants = {t for t, f in token_freq.items() if f >= MAX_VARIANT_FREQ}\r\n    variants = {t for t, f in token_freq.items() if f <= MIN_VARIANT_FREQ}\r\n    uncertain = {t for t, f in token_freq.items() \r\n                 if MIN_VARIANT_FREQ < f < MAX_VARIANT_FREQ}\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"invariants\": invariants,\r\n        \"variants\": variants,\r\n        \"uncertain\": uncertain,\r\n        \"token_freq\": token_freq,\r\n        \"n_pulses\": n_pulses\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(analysis: Dict, pulse_blocks: List[Dict]) -> Dict[str, set]:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what should be in next pulse based on\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:47:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338583172}}
