{"type":"message","id":"b62f6e4f","parentId":"f7fcfff8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:49:58.872Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d71fyfbewy5g_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 034914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Pending actions include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\n- Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n  - Next action: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n  - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step appears to be implementing the TIC classifier on pulse logs. This is a well-defined task that can be started.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory to see what pulse files exist.\r\n\r\nActually, I should implement the TIC classifier. The key insight is that causal structure IS invariant structure. The classifier needs to:\r\n1. Analyze pulse logs for invariant vs variant patterns\r\n2. Test classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nI should create a script or implementation that does this. Let me create a TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nLooking at the task - I need to pick ONE concrete action. The TIC experiment is the next logical step. I'll create the TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me write a PowerShell or Python script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariants (patterns that persist across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variants (patterns that change)\r\n4. Classifies and measures accuracy\r\n5. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI'll create this as a new file in research/ or as a script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step for Phase 1 advancement. I have pulse logs available and need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,\r\n    [int]$MinOccurrence = 3\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$LogsDir = Join-Path $ScriptDir \"..\\logs\"\r\n$OutputFile = Join-Path $ScriptDir \"tic_results.md\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($f in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $pulses += Get-Content $f.FullName -Raw\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($pulses.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract structural elements from each pulse\r\nfunction Extract-Patterns($content) {\r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Observations = @()\r\n        Mutations = @()\r\n        FileRefs = @()\r\n        Metrics = @{}\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references\r\n    if ($content -match '(?sm)^\\##\\s*(.+?)$') {\r\n        $patterns.Goals += $matches[1].Trim()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $fileMatches = [regex]::Matches($content, '([\\w\\-\\/\\.]+\\.(md|ps1|txt|json|csv))')\r\n    foreach ($m in $fileMatches) {\r\n        $patterns.FileRefs += $m.Value\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key metrics\r\n    if ($content -match '(\\d+)%') {\r\n        $patterns.Metrics['Percentage'] = [int]$matches[1]\r\n    }\r\n    if ($content -match '~(.+?)s') {\r\n        $patterns.Metrics['Duration'] = $matches[1]\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Analyze patterns across pulses\r\n$allPatterns = @()\r\nforeach ($p in $pulses) {\r\n    $allPatterns += Extract-Patterns $p\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify INVARIANTS (appear in most pulses)\r\n$invariantCandidates = @{}\r\nforeach ($p in $allPatterns) {\r\n    foreach ($f in $p.FileRefs) {\r\n        if (-not $invariantCandidates.ContainsKey($f)) {\r\n            $invariantCandidates[$f] = 0\r\n        }\r\n        $invariantCandidates[$f]++\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$invariants = $invariantCandidates.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value -ge $MinOccurrence } | Sort-Object Value -Descending\r\n$variants = $invariantCandidates.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value -lt $MinOccurrence } | Sort-Object Value -Descending\r\n\r\n# Calculate classification accuracy\r\n$totalPatterns = $invariantCandidates.Count\r\n$correctClassifications = $invariants.Count + $variants.Count\r\n$classificationAccuracy = if ($totalPatterns -gt 0) { ($correctClassifications / $totalPatterns) * 100 } else { 0 }\r\n\r\n# Generate report\r\n$report = @\"\r\n# TIC Experiment Results\r\n**Date:** $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\r\n**Pulses Analyzed:** $($pulses.Count)\r\n\r\n## Invariant Patterns (≥$MinOccurrence occurrences)\r\n| Pattern | Occurrences |\r\n|---------|-------------|\r\n$(($invariants | ForEach-Object\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:49:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338598871}}
